description: India's supersonic prowess is taking flight from Lucknow with the inauguration of a state-of-the-art BrahMos Aerospace Integration and Testing Facility. This 200-acre complex is set to become the epicentre for producing the formidable BrahMos cruise missile, catering to surging domestic and international demand, including significant export orders.
title: BrahMos and beyond: How UP is becoming India’s defence capital

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: An Indian-origin Singaporean man, Kokulananthan Mohan, faces charges for a false terrorist threat at St Joseph's Church. He allegedly placed a fabricated device, causing services to be cancelled. Preliminary probes indicate he acted alone, with no terror or religious motive found. Mohan is undergoing psychiatric evaluation.
title: Church scare in Singapore: Indian-origin man charged over terror threat

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Power couple Ranveer Singh and Deepika Padukone turned heads at the Mumbai airport in coordinated black and grey winter wear. Ranveer, basking in his film's massive box office success, was cheered by photographers. The spy thriller is now his career's biggest hit, nearing Rs 1,000 crore globally. Deepika, busy with upcoming projects, joined him for the stylish airport spotting.
title: 'Dhurandhar' and Deepika : Paparazzi tease Ranveer at airport

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Gold price prediction today: Gold prices are poised for a significant surge, potentially reaching ₹138,000-₹140,000, according to Manav Modi.  Silver has already seen remarkable gains, exceeding 120% year-to-date.  Despite record highs, investors are advised to buy on dips, with key support levels at ₹132,000.
title: Gold price prediction: What is the price outlook in the coming days?

author: RAHUL SINGH
description: A survivor of the 2016 Bulandshahr gang rape, now studying law, shared her family's decade-long ordeal of harassment and relocation after the brutal attack. Conviction of five men offers hope, but the trauma and its impact on their lives and livelihoods remain profound.
title: 'I remember every face': 2016 UP highway gang rape survivors recount years of trauma

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: India and New Zealand have signed a historic free trade agreement, concluding negotiations in just nine months. The pact aims to boost trade and investment, with both leaders confident bilateral trade could double in five years. It includes significant market access for Indian services and tariff reductions on New Zealand exports.
title: India-New Zealand FTA finalised: PM Modi speaks to Christopher Luxon

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Kerala Chief Minister Pinarayi Vijayan assured strict action and justice for Ram Narayan Bakel, a Dalit migrant labourer from Chhattisgarh, who was beaten to death by a mob in Walayar, Palakkad. A special investigation team has been formed to probe the incident, which the CM termed unacceptable in a progressive society.
title: Kerala mob lynching: CM vows strict action after mob beats Dalit labourer to death

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Microsoft CEO Satya Nadella is accelerating AI development by empowering frontline technical employees. He's implemented weekly AI accelerator meetings where junior staff present directly to him, bypassing senior management. This unconventional approach aims to foster unfiltered insights and drive the company's AI transformation with urgency.
title: Microsoft’s new AI huddle: Nadella starts weekly meeting for engineers; no senior manager allowed

author: ARANI BASU
description: Sanju Samson's long-awaited T20 World Cup opening spot comes after a decade of uncertainty and a revolving door of wicketkeepers. Despite strong performances, he faced confusion and batting order shifts, highlighting the team management's struggle for consistency in selecting their T20I wicketkeeper and openers.
title: T20 WC: Finally Samson's moment of clarity? India's T20 'opener' looks to rise above chaos

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: TRAI has urged broadcasters to comply with the 12-minute-per-hour advertising cap, despite the rule being under judicial review. The regulator insists the regulation remains applicable, even as the Delhi High Court has restrained coercive action. Broadcasters are concerned about the enforcement due to existing financial pressures and declining revenues.
title: Trai's '12-minute-per-hour' cap: Regulator asks broadcasters to comply with limit

author: TNN
title: Yearend special: Newsmakers who spiced up 2025

author: PRANTIK PRABAL ROY
description: Christen Goff is navigating motherhood by creating two distinct yet personal homes in Los Angeles and Michigan for her and daughter Romy.  She thoughtfully designs each space to reflect its location and their evolving family identity.  Despite the challenges of a newborn and dual residences, Christen finds joy and belonging in this new chapter.
title: Jared Goff’s wife Christen reveals motherhood-inspired makeover of family homes

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: A Hindu garment worker was beaten to death by a mob in Bangladesh after allegations of hurting religious sentiments spread. Police admitted that a massive traffic jam and a furious crowd prevented them from reaching the victim, Dipu Chandra Das, in time. Authorities suggest a delayed call for help may have cost him his life.
title: ‘Blocked by the crowd’: Bangladesh police on mob lynching of Hindu worker Dipu; blame 'late call'

author: SANJAY SHARMA
description: The Deputy Commissioner Gurugram has implemented revised office timings and a work from home advisory in response to deteriorating air quality. The Commission for Air Quality Management (CAQM) has invoked Stage-IV of the Graded Response Action Plan (GRAP) in Delhi-NCR. State Government offices will operate from 09:30 AM to 05:30 PM, municipal offices from 08:30 AM to 04:30 PM, and private offices are advised to allow 50% staff to work remotely until further notice, as posted on X.
title: GRAP Stage-IV in Gurugram explained: Timings changed, WFH pushed for offices

author: ROHIT KHANNA AND ROSHAN GUPTA
description: The lynching of Dipu Das in Bangladesh has ignited protests across Bengal, with Hindu organizations condemning the "barbarism" against minorities.  Das, a Hindu from a lower caste, was allegedly targeted for a promotion, with accusations of social media posts used as a pretext.  Activists are demanding action and a boycott of Bangladeshi goods.
title: Bangladesh unrest: Hindu worker Dipu Das's lynching sparks outrage in Bengal

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Mars' abundant ice offers a revolutionary solution for future human settlements. Scientists propose using this frozen water as a primary building material, providing crucial insulation against extreme temperatures and harmful radiation. This sustainable approach significantly reduces reliance on Earth-based supplies, making Mars colonization more practical and cost-effective, paving the way for a new era of space exploration.
title: Building Mars colonies with ice: How scientists plan to make it possible

author: TOI Education
description: CBSE has announced an orientation programme for schools under its Hub and Spoke School Model to strengthen collaboration, resource sharing and student well-being. Scheduled for December 26, 2025, in Jaipur, the programme will bring together school leaders and counsellors to improve implementation, coordination and counselling practices. Registration is free, with limited seats.
title: CBSE releases important notice on Hub & Spoke School Model; announces orientation programme

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Three men will face trial next year for allegedly stealing valuable silverware and tableware from the French President's residence. The items, including Sèvres porcelain and Baccarat glasses, are valued between €15,000 and €40,000. Investigations led to a palace steward, his partner, and a Louvre guard, with many items recovered. The trial is set for February 26.
title: French presidential palace robbery: Silverware worth thousands of euros stolen

author: SAMAD HOQUE
description: A Rapido cab driver was arrested within hours for allegedly misbehaving with a woman, hurling abuses, and dropping her on a deserted road late in the evening. The incident occurred after the woman requested the driver to lower loud music, leading to an aggressive confrontation and her feeling unsafe.
title: 'Is this your father’s car?': Rapido driver assaults woman, hurls abuses in Gurgaon

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Police in Jammu and Kashmir recovered a Chinese-made weapon-mountable telescope from a six-year-old boy in Sidhra, who reportedly found it in a garbage dump. A separate search operation was launched in Udhampur after terrorists allegedly stole food from a house before fleeing into a forest, days after a deadly encounter.
title: J&K: 6-yr old boy finds 'toy' in garbage, turns out to be 'Chinese-made weapon-mountable telescope'

author: SAURABH SINHA
description: Mid air scare: Air India flight returns to Delhi after 'one engine shutdown'
title: Mid-air scare: Mumbai bound Air India flight returns to Delhi after 'one engine shutdown'

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Stock market today: Nifty50 and BSE Sensex, the Indian equity benchmark indices, rallied strongly in trade on Monday. While Nifty50 was above 26,100, BSE Sensex surged over 450 points.
title: Stock market today: Nifty50 above 26,100; BSE Sensex up over 450 points

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Pakistan's chief selector Aaqib Javed revealed he's studied India's white-ball success to improve Pakistan's cricket structure. He stressed that quality talent, fostered by robust infrastructure and competition, is key to sustained success, not just individual brilliance. Javed expressed optimism about Pakistan's current team, especially with the upcoming T20 World Cup in familiar conditions.
title: 'Studied India's success': How can Pakistan's cricket be fixed? Selector reveals blueprint

author: GAURAV GUPTA
description: Hardik Pandya's stellar comeback from injury in the T20I series against South Africa has cemented his status as India's T20 MVP. His explosive batting and crucial wickets, including a 16-ball fifty, were instrumental in India's 3-1 series win. South Africa's coach lauded Pandya's impact, highlighting his vital role in the series.
title: T20 WC: Hardik Pandya hits top gear - Explosive return vs SA shows why he remains India's MVP

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Stock market recommendations: Motilal Oswal Financial Services has identified Astra Microwave Products and Crompton Greaves Consumer Electricals as top stock picks for the week of December 22, 2025. Astra Microwave is poised for growth in defense electronics, while Crompton aims to expand its market share in consumer electricals, particularly with its acquisition of Butterfly Gandhimathi Appliances.
title: Top stocks to buy: Stock recommendations for this week - check list

author: PRANTIK PRABAL ROY
description: Steelers quarterback Aaron Rodgers has found unexpected peace in his marriage to Brittani.  Unlike his previous public relationships, Brittani values privacy.  Rodgers credits his wife with providing unconditional love and stability.  This new chapter sees a calmer, more focused Rodgers as he navigates his final NFL years.  His teammates and coaches notice the positive change.
title: Who is Brittani? Aaron Rodgers’ wife as Steelers QB marriage mystery deepens

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Delhi experienced hazy skies on Monday, with the overall air quality falling into the 'very poor' category. Four areas, including Narela and Bawana, recorded 'severe' AQI levels exceeding 400. This follows a similar trend from Sunday, when the city's AQI was also in the very poor range.
title: Delhi air pollution crisis: AQI remains very poor; 4 areas slip into ‘severe’ zone

author: KANGKAN KALITA AND B SRIDHAR
description: Elephant deaths in Assam tragically rose to eight after a Rajdhani Express collision, prompting a speed restriction for trains. Meanwhile, Jharkhand's railway division cancelled eight trains due to heightened wild elephant movement near tracks, marking the third consecutive cancellation to prioritize animal safety.
title: Elephant toll in Assam rises to 8; Jharkhand cancels 8 trains

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Former Bangladesh PM Sheikh Hasina reacted to the death of student leader Sharif Usman Hadi, highlighting the deteriorating law and order in what she called the reality of Yunus’s Bangladesh. She accused the Muhammad Yunus-led interim government of failing to protect minorities and allowing violence to escalate across the country.
title: 'India sees chaos': Hasina on 'reality of Yunus' Bangladesh'; blames interim govt

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: At least 15 people died when an inter-province passenger bus veered off a toll road on Java, Indonesia, early Monday. The bus, en route from Jakarta to Yogyakarta with 34 passengers, struck a barrier and overturned. The cause of the crash and the condition of the injured are still being investigated.
title: Indonesia bus crash: Driver loses control, hits barrier; 15 killed

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Former India captain Rohit Sharma revealed he considered quitting cricket after the 2023 ODI World Cup final loss to Australia. The emotional toll of the defeat, after investing heavily since becoming captain, left him feeling drained. It took months of recovery and self-reflection to regain his passion for the sport.

The yellow metal's appeal as a safe haven has been bolstered by geopolitical tensions and central bank buying, with silver also experiencing significant gains.

description: A 17-year-old girl was allegedly gang-raped by three men from her village who lured her into fields. The accused, who had previously threatened to release compromising videos, coerced her into meeting them. The girl reported the incident the next morning after being held overnight.
